  "description": [
    "ALEXANDRIA sahtjuy morning skpr 15 is9 We aie sorry to see that our friends of the opposition party are again bringing into vogue as a party catch word the old cry of manifest destmy and endeavoring to ue it for the sake of making political capital and exciting the cupidity and desire of the people for the acqui ston of new territory If with the manifest tendency which our opponents obviously have to an acquiescence in the doctrine of swallow ing every country upon which we can lay our han Is they had succeeded at the last presiden tial election in elevating Gen Cass to the office of President we do not know but that this manifest destiny would have been incoi porated into the thirty nine articles of the or thodox Democratic church or at least been put tip as one of the main props and pillars of the Democratic platform Possibly the resolu tions of 9 would have paled their ineffectual fires before the blighter effulgence of this new er and more serviceable principle Failing however in the election of Gen Cass we had hoped that the manifest destiny idea had gone to the tomb ot the Capulets"
